.TH "phy_init_eee" 9 "phy_init_eee" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phy_init_eee \- init and check the EEE feature
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phy_init_eee
.BI "(struct phy_device *phydev "  ","
.BI "bool clk_stop_enable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phydev" 12
target phy_device struct
.IP "clk_stop_enable" 12
PHY may stop the clock during LPI
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
it checks if the Energy-Efficient Ethernet (EEE)
is supported by looking at the MMD registers 3.20 and 7.60/61
and it programs the MMD register 3.0 setting the "Clock stop enable"
bit if required.
